<TITLE> Spanish king urges unity in fight against terrorism </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Madrid, Dec 25 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Spain's King Juan Carlos appealed in his Christmas message on Monday for unity against terrorism after a year of bitter debate on how to defeat the Basque separatist group ETA. The king's remarks came after Spain's Socialist government and the conservative Popular Party opposition have clashed in recent months over how to deal with ETA. The government has accused the conservative Popular Party (PP) opposition of breaking a cross-party consensus on the issue. The PP has backed street protests accusing the government of surrendering to ETA, which has killed more than 800 people in its fight for an independent Basque nation. "We need, as soon as possible, a culture of unity that delivers on the commitment of all democrats to definitively bring terrorism to an end," Juan Carlos said
